						               													<description>Compete to have the best stall with the best combination of monsters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Socks Monster is a competitive game, in which we will have to take into account both sides of the cards: On one side we find the monsters and on the other the socks. The goal of the game is to finish with the most points at the end of the game, thanks to the connections of the socks and the bonuses of the monsters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the beginning of the game two cards are dealt to each player and with the remaining cards four equal draw decks are made showing the sides of the socks.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In turns, the player draws a card from any draw deck and then plays a card on the table. We must always start on our first turn with a monster and then follow the placement rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;We will be playing cards forming our stall and making chains of socks to be able to lower other monsters. The socks are connected and superimposed following the placement rules and the requests of the monsters.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;At the end of the game we will get points for the correct connections of the socks, the score bonuses of the monsters and we will subtract points for the stinky socks.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In addition, the game has a small variant, where the weather symbols come into play and add more interaction and bite to the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
